headline: Oil Stocks Sink Ahead of OPEC Meeting
summary: Shares of U.S. oil producers are weighing on the S&P 500, falling sharply Wednesday amid speculation that the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries and its market allies might decide to boost output and exacerbate a global fuel glut when the cartel meets this weekend.
